<span id="freeTextContainer12980814055411807822">Reading Kahlil&apos;s words is like living in spiritual bliss. Three different stories mingled with philosophy and the divine love. After all, it&apos;s not the stories that Gibran says are beautiful, the way he says it, and the words he uses to express make them beautiful. Gibran, the magician of words.<br/><br/><i>
  <b>In the opinion of the head priest, a man cannot become a monk unless he is blind and ignorant, senseless and dumb. I left the convent because I am a sensible man who can see, feel, and hear.</b>
