        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4365755898" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1035530528401918734"><blockquote>&quot;Shall we meet evil with evil and say this the Law? Shall we fight corruption with greater corruption and say this is the Rule? Shall we conquer crimes with more crimes and say this is Justice?&quot;</blockquote><br/><br/>I loved this collection. Kahlil Gibran&apos;s lyrical writing is very enjoyable to read. These three short stories dive into the hypocrisies and corruptions of society&apos;s authorities and religious figures. This book was banned and publicly burned in Lebanon, yet Khalil&apos;s response was optimistic as it meant he c</span>
  <span id="freeText1035530528401918734" style="display:none"><blockquote>"Shall we meet evil with evil and say this the Law? Shall we fight corruption with greater corruption and say this is the Rule? Shall we conquer crimes with more crimes and say this is Justice?"</blockquote><br /><br />I loved this collection. Kahlil Gibran's lyrical writing is very enjoyable to read. These three short stories dive into the hypocrisies and corruptions of society's authorities and religious figures. This book was banned and publicly burned in Lebanon, yet Khalil's response was optimistic as it meant he can begin a second publication. Good for him. <br /></span>
