<div id="review_21724534" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/21724534" />
    <a title="Just_jenn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1106884-just-jenn"><img alt="Just_jenn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1237647691p2/1106884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/21724534?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Just_jenn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Just_jenn" href="/user/show/1106884-just-jenn">Just_jenn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780806503646" href="/book/show/376502.Spirits_Rebellious">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer21724534" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17969796977895291277">Loved this first two stories in particular. One reminded me of my own story of love and loss and found again. The other, a remarkable exploration into the idea that although dates and fashions and certain hardships change, humans and our subsequent problems with each other and our governments remain the same throughout the generations.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


